1. mapping_node.py

PURPOSE:

Main custom mapping node. It currently does:

- subscribe to D455 depth image

- subscribe to D455 camera info

- subscribe to /odom

- project sampled depth pixels into 3D

- transform points into odom

- apply height filter

- perform Bresenham free-space carving

- publish 2D occupancy grid on /thesis_mapping/grid_map


RUN Command:

cd ~/UVC_ws/vf_robot_model_ros2
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
source install/setup.bash
ros2 run thesis_mapping mapping_node


When it SHOULD RUN:

Run this when need to,

- generate your custom 2D map

- visualize /thesis_mapping/grid_map in RViz

- test mapping logic changes


What should be RUNNING with it:

- Gazebo simulation
- TF/robot state publishers
- /odom publisher


What should NOT be running:

- octomap_server

- depth_to_cloud.launch.py



2. setup.py

PURPOSE:

Package setup file for mapping.

- registers the Python package

- installs launch files

- registers executable


When it is USED:

During build,

cd ~/UVC_ws/vf_robot_model_ros2
colcon build
source install/setup.bash


When need to REBUILD:

Rebuild after changing,

- mapping_node.py

- lauunch files

- executable registration

- package installation paths



3. depth_to_cloud.launch.py

PURPOSE:

Launches 'depth_image_proc/point_cloud_xyz_radial_node' to convert:

- /d455/depth/d455_depth/depth/image_raw

- /d455/depth/d455_depth/camera_info

into:

- /thesis_mapping/d455_points


COMMAND to RUN:

cd ~/UVC_ws/vf_robot_model_ros2
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
source install/setup.bash
ros2 launch thesis_mapping depth_to_cloud.launch.py


When to be USED:

Use this only when you want to test the alternate pipeline,

- Depth image + camera info → point cloud


Not used currently.





